### 5. `OpinionsReplyCard` — Shared `showReply` State Across All Rendered Replies - Confidence: 85

**File:** `client/src/components/SidebarOpinions/OpinionsCardRepy.jsx` lines 18, 118-120

The `showReply` boolean at line 18 is a single piece of state at the component level, but it is used inside the `.map()` over `opinioData` (lines 79-192). When **any** reply's "Show N replies" button is clicked, `setShowReply(prev => !prev)` toggles one shared boolean, which causes **every reply in the list** to react to it — all nested `<OpinionsReplyCard>` instances will mount or unmount simultaneously, triggering N waterfall queries where only 1 was intended.

```jsx
// line 18 — one flag for all replies
const [showReply, setShowReply] = useState(false);

// line 118-120 — inside opinioData.map(), toggles the shared flag
<button onClick={() => setShowReply(prev => !prev)}>
    {showReply ? 'Hide' : 'Show'} {opinion.reply_count} replies
</button>

// line 185 — ALL nested cards mount/unmount when showReply flips
{showReply && <OpinionsReplyCard opinionId={opinion.id} depth={depth + 1} />}
```

**Fix — track open state per-reply ID:**
```js
const [openReplies, setOpenReplies] = useState(new Set());
const toggleReply = (id) => setOpenReplies(prev => {
    const next = new Set(prev);
    next.has(id) ? next.delete(id) : next.add(id);
    return next;
});

// In render:
{openReplies.has(opinion.id) && <OpinionsReplyCard opinionId={opinion.id} depth={depth + 1} />}
```

